    narr:narration """This hub aggregates [phrasing assessments](narr:Rubric_Assess_Phrasing) across organizational touchpoints, documenting a consistent reliance on high-agency idiolect and domain-specific verbs. The thematic span moves from [technical process descriptors](narr:Rubric_Phrasing_ScarletDame) like 'steering vector' and 'continuation machines' to [GTM-oriented metaphors](narr:RubricAssess_Phrasing_GTM) such as 'builder trap' and 'clean to sell.' Assessments highlight how [canonical product terms](narr:Assess_Phrasing_RevenueModelTAM) like 'collective memory' anchor brand identity, while [conversational idiolect](narr:Assessment_Phrasing_YC)—including 'separated at birth' and 'I know Kung Fu'—is deployed to signal chemistry. The [founder-facing narrative](narr:Rubric_Phrasing_FounderBetaUser) leverages distinct metaphors like 'gods of Olympus' and 'MCP-native,' contrasting with the [operational verbs](narr:Rubric_Phrasing_PilotPlan) of 'compile,' 'query,' and 'ingest' found in pilot planning. Across these artifacts, phrasing serves as a strategic tool for [thematic anchoring](narr:RubricAssess_Phrasing), moving between the technical substrate and the social dynamics of adoption.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Assess_Phrasing_RevenueModelTAM> ;
